//////////////////////////////////////////////////////
 Softbrain Vertical Infrastructure -- RISCV-ISA-SIM 
////////////////////////////////////////////////////

RISCV-GNU-Tooolchain: Handle - Tony

Modifications here are to the assembler to support new instructions.  Opcode MASK/MATCH'ers
are generated from riscv-parseopcodes script.



The following is an optional step which may or many not reduce compilation time.  Tony
does not recommend it as it is a hack, and actually doesn't help speed things up much.
What is more effective is actually just compiling NOT ON AFS.  Use a scratch drive if
possible.

************************************************************************************
Change the lines with curl for Makefile generated for gnu-toolchain
(curl takes forver to download the gnu source -- Use wget)

Replace the fololowing Makefile lines - 
#cd src && (cat $(DISTDIR)/$(subst src/original-,,$@)-$($(subst src/original-,,$@)_version).tar.gz || /usr/bin/curl -o - --ftp-pasv $($(subst src/original-,,$@)_url)) | tar zxf -

-----WITH------

cd src && (cat $(DISTDIR)/$(subst src/original-,,$@)-$($(subst src/original-,,$@)_version).tar.gz || /usr/bin/wget -t 100 $($(subst src/original-,,$@)_url))
gunzip $(subst original-,,$@)-$($(subst src/original-,,$@)_version).tar.gz
tar -xvf $(subst original-,,$@)-$($(subst src/original-,,$@)_version).tar -C src
**********************************************************************************

This sb-vertical branch tracks the upstream origin/sb-vertical branch
